<p>On Monday, Hamas handed the 20 remaining living Israeli hostages to the Red Cross under a U.S.-brokered truce, while Israel released over 1,900 Palestinian prisoners and detainees — nearly 2,000 in total — including 250 people serving life sentences [apnews.com#1][npr.org#1][bbc.com#1]. Hours later in Sharm el‑Sheikh, President Trump and the leaders of Egypt, Qatar and Turkey signed a declaration as guarantors to cement the ceasefire and move toward a next phase addressing Gaza’s future governance and reconstruction [newarab.com#1][thehindu.com#2][scmp.com#1][cbsnews.com#1][mercopress.com#1]. Trump also addressed Israel’s parliament, declaring the Gaza war “over,” though Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu did not attend the Egypt summit [washingtonpost.com#1][nytimes.com#2][timesofisrael.com#1]. The UN and aid groups say Gaza still urgently needs lifesaving assistance amid widespread displacement and destruction, even as planning and aid flows begin to ramp up [theguardian.com#2][thehindu.com#5][france24.com#3][newarab.com#3]. On Tuesday, Israel’s military said it fired on suspects who crossed a pullback boundary in northern Gaza, while local authorities reported six Palestinians killed — a reminder of the truce’s fragility [reuters.com#1].</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/lFFdmB2-6qg4d6il_J1mhbi1heW3QyPE8TEKK5Lq_dXlmJqxmFcWKnU2HrxxJm85TsR6xmHkiLu45VheztwBME4jgwcCcdwblGCeiXG5eZjCzjt_nByx15ehPJxsACCOAZRedcoWLGaLvLlLXm3TOX86QDS624_TL5bmIXLui4WFPBL3KAsCy3E8GAR-idTGNKDGnwHHCVpTtdfzYntf3hZX8u3AOVkCpc2QZwIUw9bxSL2bHhuHwQApbfRZtC5358pEE7h96Bmu82B2yD8mf13JxhyEE9WDYzGJOVEDItk08zE5PVPtpwzS0dHDUvXM5NkApzQ3gkEAjJfoATc4Eu8bSR04-A01lxS4dAJda5rzJrIy5bQ8NdV-BYo1Lqs37lUIxHc3_DDjXqlDq9g5p_LwfXn-2790G0wIQ_sZi203nlEZj2mroHPCGGgCrBt4eDjgA-b6vcoYO43oqy22rU7qPD9QA9tdQdtGWPd7VGT4MtcswtN0P6I-oLkBXvEJWAgm2tR-4kc' alt='President Trump speaks as world leaders gather in Sharm el‑Sheikh to sign the Gaza declaration.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Swap details: Hamas freed 20 living